The following Merline parameters are set within the <sim>Params.py file under merlinParams

ROUTE----------------
merlinParams.route -- 0 is 1st direct route,
         	      1 is 2nd direct route,
	              2 is 1st valiant route,
	              3 is 2nd valiant route,
	              set to any other number to disable

RUNTYPE----------------
merlinParams.runtype -- 0 - generates routing table
	                1 - loads the routing table from file and does adaptive routing for failed links
	                2 - normal run

RT_FNAME-------------------
merlinParams.rt_filename -- filename of the routing table

PORT_FNAME----------------------
merlinParams.downPort_filename -- filename of the list of disabled ports


To change the values, they can either be changed in the <sim>Params.py file or by command line as follows:

sst ./emberLoad.py --model-options='--simConfig <simFile> --param merlin:merlinParams.route=<int>  --param merlin:merlinParams.runtype=<int>  --param merlin:merlinParams.rt_filename=<string> --param merlin:merlinParams.downPort_filename=<string>'



